  Dialogue:
  - The ephemerality of life brought an indescribable anguish to <color=purple>William</color>'s
    soul.
  - To think that his existence would end forever was a terrifying idea for him,
    but the music <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> played changed his perspective on
    ephemerality.
  - That song would soon come to an end and become a unique moment in <color=green>Akasha</color>'s
    memories. It was a wonderful experience to hear the melody, feel a damp wind
    on his skin, smell the herbs around him and balance <color=blue>Mana</color>
    through breathing.
  - Realizing the value of air, the most common symbol of ephemerality, <color=purple>William</color>
    began to imagine the brevity of his life as a rare gem.
  - What made his existence special on the akashic plane was precisely the rarity
    of his life and those special moments.
  - '"I''m happy? This is not right".'
  - '"I must not forget why I joined the Guild."'
  - What did you think of this song?
  - I didn't think much of it.
  - Oh, I'm sorry...
  - Every wind had a feeling in <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color>'s opinion. According
    to him, the <color=blue>Mana</color> determined the nature of the wind, a summer
    breeze could be a boon to one who was at peace with himself, while the same wind
    would be torturous to those who rejected the flow of the world.
  - <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color>'s instruments were stored under a sad, lonely wind.
  - "No\u2026"
  - I lied.
  - "The music was beautiful, it made me really\u2026 happy."
  - "\u201CWhy am I saying this?\u201D"
  - Then it's your turn to play, <color=purple>William</color>.
  DialogueBR:
  - "A efemeridade da vida trazia uma ang\xFAstia indescrit\xEDvel para a alma de
    <color=purple>William</color>."
  - "Pensar que sua exist\xEAncia terminaria para sempre era uma ideia aterrorizante
    para ele, mas a m\xFAsica que <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> tocava mudou sua
    perspectiva sobre a efemeridade."
  - "Aquela m\xFAsica logo teria um fim e se tornaria um momento \xFAnico nas mem\xF3rias
    de <color=green>Akasha</color>. Era uma experi\xEAncia maravilhosa ouvir a melodia,
    sentir um vento \xFAmido em sua pele, cheirar as ervas ao seu redor e equilibrar
    o Mana atrav\xE9s da respira\xE7\xE3o."
  - "Percebendo o valor do ar, s\xEDmbolo mais comum da efemeridade, <color=purple>William</color>
    come\xE7ou a imaginar a brevidade de sua vida como uma joia rara."
  - "O que tornava sua exist\xEAncia especial no plano ak\xE1shico era justamente
    a raridade de sua vida e daqueles momentos especiais."
  - "\u201CEu estou feliz? Isso n\xE3o est\xE1 certo\u201D."
  - "\u201CN\xE3o devo me esquecer do motivo de eu ter me juntado \xE0 Guilda\u201D."
  - "O que voc\xEA achou dessa m\xFAsica?"
  - "N\xE3o achei nada de especial."
  - "Oh, eu sinto muito\u2026 "
  - "Cada vento tinha um sentimento na opini\xE3o de <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color>.
    Segundo ele, o Mana determinava a natureza do vento, uma brisa de ver\xE3o poderia
    ser uma d\xE1diva para quem estivesse em paz consigo mesmo, enquanto o mesmo
    vento seria torturante para aqueles que rejeitassem o fluxo do mundo."
  - "Os instrumentos de <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> foram guardados sob um vento
    triste e solit\xE1rio."
  - "N\xE3o\u2026"
  - Eu menti.
  - "A m\xFAsica estava linda, ela me deixou realmente\u2026 feliz."
  - "\u201CPor que eu estou falando isso?\u201D"
  - "Ent\xE3o \xE9 a sua vez de tocar, <color=purple>William</color>."
